title: GU0700_T
source_name_ch1: CD45+ immune cells from renal tumor
extract_protocol_ch1: Viable (Hoechst-), immune (CD45+) single-cell suspensions generated from three ccRCC tumor samples and peripheral blood were sorted on a FACS ARIA sorter (BD Biosciences) for lymphoid and myeloid lineages. The cells were sorted into ice-cold 1x PBS + 0.04% non-acetylated bovine-serum albumin (New England BioLabs). Sorted cells were counted and viability as assessed using the MoxiGoII counter (Orflo Technologies). Single cells were re-suspended at 1000 cells/ul with a viability > 90%. Libraries were generated using using the Chromium Single Cell 5-prime Enrichment Kit and sequenced on the Illumina HiSeq 4000
data_processing: 10x Data was processed with the Cell Ranger pipeline, version 2.2
